quran[9]{c,v,t}:
  22,56,On that Day the Kingdom will be that of Allahâ€™s; He will judge between them; so those who have embraced the true faith and done good deeds shall enter the gardens of delight
  22,57,but the unbelievers who have denied Our revelations shall receive a disgraceful punishment
  22,58,"As for those who migrated for the sake of Allah and afterwards were killed or died, Allah will make a generous provision for them; certainly Allah is the One Who is the best Provider"
  22,59,"He will admit them to a place with which they shall be well pleased; for Allah is All-Knowing, Most Lenient"
  22,60,"Thus shall it be! He that retaliates equal to the infliction he received and then is wronged again, will most certainly be helped by Allah; surely Allah is the One Who is All-Forbearing, Most Forgiving"
  22,61,"That is because it is Allah Who causes the night to pass into the day, and the day into the night, Allah is indeed All-Hearing, Most Observing"
  22,62,"That is because Allah is the One Who is Real; and all those deities besides Him, whom they invoke, are false; indeed it is Allah Who is the Supreme, the Great"
  22,63,"Do you not see that Allah sends down water from the sky so the land becomes green? Surely Allah is the Benignant, Aware"
  22,64,"To Him belongs all that is in the heavens and the earth; surely Allah is the One Who is the Self-sufficient, the Praiseworthy"